This paper deals with user association in millimeter-wave networks, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses optimization frameworks and algorithms, which are related to computer science and optimization theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also discusses spatial multiplexing and hybrid transceiver architecture, which are related to signal processing and communication systems, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. The paper also discusses the satisfaction of user-specific rate requirements, which is related to system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of different user association approaches, which is related to performance evaluation and analysis, making cs.COM (Computers and Society) a possible category.
